```

---

## SQL Completo para Supabase

```sql
-- ============================================================
-- ENUMS
-- ============================================================
CREATE TYPE school_level AS ENUM ('primaria', 'secundaria', 'terciario', 'universitario');
CREATE TYPE school_shift AS ENUM ('mañana', 'tarde', 'noche', 'vespertino');
CREATE TYPE enrollment_status AS ENUM ('activo', 'inactivo');
CREATE TYPE assignment_status AS ENUM ('borrador', 'asignado', 'entregado');
CREATE TYPE submission_status AS ENUM ('pendiente', 'entregado', 'corregido');
CREATE TYPE assignment_type AS ENUM ('tp', 'evaluacion', 'actividad');
CREATE TYPE grade_period AS ENUM ('1er_trimestre', '2do_trimestre', '3er_trimestre', 'final');
CREATE TYPE grade_category AS ENUM ('tp', 'parcial', 'concepto', 'participacion', 'examen');
CREATE TYPE lesson_plan_type AS ENUM ('anual', 'unidad', 'clase', 'armani');

-- ============================================================
-- 1. TEACHERS (perfil del docente, extendido de auth.users)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.teachers (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    full_name   TEXT NOT NULL,
    email       TEXT NOT NULL,
    avatar_url  TEXT,
    preferences JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 2. SCHOOLS (escuelas del docente)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.schools (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    teacher_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.teachers(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    name        TEXT NOT NULL,
    address     TEXT,
    phone       TEXT,
    level       school_level,
    shift       school_shift,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 3. COURSES (materias/cursos dentro de una escuela)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.courses (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    school_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.schools(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    name        TEXT NOT NULL,
    year        TEXT,              -- "1er Año", "2do Año"
    division    TEXT,              -- "A", "B", "C"
    color       TEXT DEFAULT '#6366f1',
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 4. COURSE_SCHEDULES (horarios de cada curso)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.course_schedules (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    course_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.courses(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    day_of_week SMALLINT NOT NULL CHECK (day_of_week BETWEEN 0 AND 6),
    start_time  TIME NOT NULL,
    end_time    TIME NOT NULL,
    classroom   TEXT,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 5. STUDENTS (alumnos globales del docente)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.students (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    teacher_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.teachers(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    first_name  TEXT NOT NULL,
    last_name   TEXT NOT NULL,
    dni         TEXT,
    email       TEXT,
    phone       TEXT,
    notes       TEXT,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 6. COURSE_STUDENTS (inscripción alumnos ↔ cursos)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.course_students (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    course_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.courses(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    student_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.students(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    status      enrollment_status DEFAULT 'activo',
    enrolled_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(course_id, student_id)
);

-- ============================================================
-- 7. ASSIGNMENTS (trabajos prácticos / evaluaciones)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.assignments (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    course_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.courses(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    title           TEXT NOT NULL,
    description     TEXT,
    status          assignment_status DEFAULT 'borrador',
    type            assignment_type DEFAULT 'tp',
    due_date        DATE,
    rubric          JSONB,
    attachment_urls TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 8. ASSIGNMENT_SUBMISSIONS (entregas de alumnos)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.assignment_submissions (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    assignment_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.assignments(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    student_id      UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.students(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    status          submission_status DEFAULT 'pendiente',
    file_urls       TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
    feedback        TEXT,
    submitted_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,
    graded_at       TIMESTAMPTZ,
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(assignment_id, student_id)
);

-- ============================================================
-- 9. GRADES (calificaciones)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.grades (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    course_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.courses(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    student_id      UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.students(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    assignment_id   UUID REFERENCES public.assignments(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
    value           NUMERIC(4,2) NOT NULL CHECK (value >= 0 AND value <= 10),
    period          grade_period NOT NULL,
    category        grade_category DEFAULT 'tp',
    observations    TEXT,
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 10. LESSON_PLANS (planificaciones)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.lesson_plans (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    course_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.courses(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    title           TEXT NOT NULL,
    type            lesson_plan_type DEFAULT 'unidad',
    content         TEXT,
    attachment_urls TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ============================================================
-- 11. LESSON_PLAN_ASSIGNMENTS (vínculo planificación ↔ TPs)
-- ============================================================
CREATE TABLE public.lesson_plan_assignments (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    lesson_plan_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.lesson_plans(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    assignment_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.assignments(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    UNIQUE(lesson_plan_id, assignment_id)
);

-- ============================================================
-- INDEXES para rendimiento
-- ============================================================
CREATE INDEX idx_schools_teacher ON public.schools(teacher_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_courses_school ON public.courses(school_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_course_schedules_course ON public.course_schedules(course_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_course_schedules_day ON public.course_schedules(day_of_week);
CREATE INDEX idx_students_teacher ON public.students(teacher_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_course_students_course ON public.course_students(course_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_course_students_student ON public.course_students(student_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_assignments_course ON public.assignments(course_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_assignments_status ON public.assignments(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_submissions_assignment ON public.assignment_submissions(assignment_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_submissions_student ON public.assignment_submissions(student_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_grades_course ON public.grades(course_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_grades_student ON public.grades(student_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_grades_period ON public.grades(period);
CREATE INDEX idx_lesson_plans_course ON public.lesson_plans(course_id);

-- ============================================================
-- ROW LEVEL SECURITY (multi-tenancy por docente)
-- ============================================================
ALTER TABLE public.teachers ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.schools ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.courses ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.course_schedules ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.students ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.course_students ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.assignments ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.assignment_submissions ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.grades ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.lesson_plans ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.lesson_plan_assignments ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Teachers: solo su propio perfil
CREATE POLICY "teachers_own" ON public.teachers
    FOR ALL USING (id = auth.uid());

-- Schools: solo las del docente autenticado
CREATE POLICY "schools_own" ON public.schools
    FOR ALL USING (teacher_id = auth.uid());

-- Courses: via school → teacher_id
CREATE POLICY "courses_own" ON public.courses
    FOR ALL USING (
        school_id IN (SELECT id FROM public.schools WHERE teacher_id = auth.uid())
    );

-- Course Schedules: via course → school → teacher
CREATE POLICY "schedules_own" ON public.course_schedules
    FOR ALL USING (
        course_id IN (
            SELECT c.id FROM public.courses c
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- Students: solo los del docente
CREATE POLICY "students_own" ON public.students
    FOR ALL USING (teacher_id = auth.uid());

-- Course Students: via course ownership
CREATE POLICY "course_students_own" ON public.course_students
    FOR ALL USING (
        course_id IN (
            SELECT c.id FROM public.courses c
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- Assignments: via course ownership
CREATE POLICY "assignments_own" ON public.assignments
    FOR ALL USING (
        course_id IN (
            SELECT c.id FROM public.courses c
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- Submissions: via assignment → course ownership
CREATE POLICY "submissions_own" ON public.assignment_submissions
    FOR ALL USING (
        assignment_id IN (
            SELECT a.id FROM public.assignments a
            JOIN public.courses c ON a.course_id = c.id
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- Grades: via course ownership
CREATE POLICY "grades_own" ON public.grades
    FOR ALL USING (
        course_id IN (
            SELECT c.id FROM public.courses c
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- Lesson Plans: via course ownership
CREATE POLICY "lesson_plans_own" ON public.lesson_plans
    FOR ALL USING (
        course_id IN (
            SELECT c.id FROM public.courses c
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- Lesson Plan Assignments: via lesson_plan ownership
CREATE POLICY "lp_assignments_own" ON public.lesson_plan_assignments
    FOR ALL USING (
        lesson_plan_id IN (
            SELECT lp.id FROM public.lesson_plans lp
            JOIN public.courses c ON lp.course_id = c.id
            JOIN public.schools s ON c.school_id = s.id
            WHERE s.teacher_id = auth.uid()
        )
    );

-- ============================================================
-- STORAGE BUCKETS (para archivos adjuntos)
-- ============================================================
-- Se crearán 2 buckets en Supabase Storage:
--   1. "assignments" → PDFs, rúbricas, archivos de TPs
--   2. "lesson-plans" → Planificaciones subidas

-- ============================================================
-- FUNCIÓN TRIGGER: updated_at automático
-- ============================================================
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
    NEW.updated_at = now();
    RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.teachers
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.schools
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.courses
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.students
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.assignments
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.grades
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.lesson_plans
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_updated_at();

-- ============================================================
-- FUNCIÓN: crear perfil de teacher al registrarse
-- ============================================================
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.handle_new_user()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
    INSERT INTO public.teachers (id, full_name, email)
    VALUES (
        NEW.id,
        COALESCE(NEW.raw_user_meta_data->>'full_name', NEW.email),
        NEW.email
    );
    RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER;

CREATE TRIGGER on_auth_user_created
    AFTER INSERT ON auth.users
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_new_user();
```

---

## Decisiones de Diseño Clave

| Decisión | Justificación |
|---|---|
| **`students.teacher_id`** en vez de global | Cada docente gestiona SU lista de alumnos. Un mismo alumno real puede existir como registros separados para distintos docentes. Simplifica RLS enormemente. |
| **`course_students` tabla pivote** | Un alumno puede estar en múltiples cursos (Geografía + Historia). Permite matriculación flexible. |
| **`grades.assignment_id` nullable** | Permite calificaciones generales (concepto, participación) que no están vinculadas a un TP específico. |
| **`lesson_plan_assignments` tabla pivote** | Una planificación puede vincular múltiples TPs y un TP puede aparecer en múltiples planificaciones. |
| **ENUMs para estados** | Garantiza integridad de datos en flujos de estado (borrador → asignado → entregado). |
| **RLS cadena `school → teacher`** | Todo dato se filtra por la cadena: `teacher_id = auth.uid()`. Las tablas hijas (courses, assignments) usan subqueries para verificar ownership vía schools. |
| **`preferences` JSONB** | Flexible para almacenar configuraciones del usuario (tema, idioma, vistas preferidas) sin alterar el schema. |

---

## Escalabilidad Futura

> [!TIP]
> Este schema ya contempla los datos necesarios para generar la **Declaración Jurada de Cargos y Actividades** cruzando:
> - `schools` (instituciones)
> - `courses` (materias con año/división)
> - `course_schedules` (horarios detallados por día)

Para la Fase 2 se pueden agregar:
- `attendance` (asistencia diaria por curso)
- `calendar_events` (agenda del docente)
- `document_templates` (plantillas de documentos burocráticos)

---

## Plan de Verificación

### Post-migración
1. Verificar que todas las tablas existen: `SELECT table_name FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema = 'public'`
2. Verificar RLS habilitado en todas las tablas
3. Verificar policies creadas: `SELECT tablename, policyname FROM pg_policies`
4. Verificar trigger `handle_new_user` existe en `auth.users`

### Funcional (manual, después de implementar la app)
- Registrar un usuario → verificar que se crea fila en `teachers`
- Crear escuela, curso con horarios, inscribir alumnos
- Crear TP con flujo de estados
- Cargar calificaciones con y sin assignment_id
- Subir archivos a storage buckets
